{eq}\begin{align}

&\frac{{40\;{\rm{ft}}}}{{10\;{\rm{ft}}}} = \frac{x}{{15.0\;{\rm{in}}}}\\[0.3 cm]

&x = \frac{{40 \times 15.0}}{{10}}\\[0.3 cm]

&x = \frac{{600}}{{10}}\\[0.3 cm]

&x = 60\;{\rm{in}}

\end{align}

{/eq}

The height of Andrea, in feet, is calculated as follows:

{eq}\begin{align}

&\left( {\frac{{60}}{{12}}} \right)\;{\rm{ft}}\\[0.3 cm]

&= 5\;{\rm{feet}}

\end{align}

{/eq}

Andrea's height in inches is

{eq}\begin{align}

& 5\;{\rm{feet}} \times 12 = 60\;{\rm{inches}}

\end{align}

{/eq}

Answer:

Andrea is 60 inches tall.

